  "title": "Forming the research question.",
  "abstract": "The most important precondition for performing a clinical research project in plastic surgery, or any other surgical subspecialty, is the need to ask the \"right question.\" Although this might seem to be an easy task, in truth it requires a lot of effort and hard work. This article addresses the key points to remember when formulating a research question.",
